description:
Background:

The team in OPPO Seattle Research Center focuses on fundamental and cutting-edge AI and robotics technologies in smart platforms (e.g., smartphones, IoT devices and robots). We are devoted to developing technologies with great potentials to positively impact people’s everyday lives in three years and beyond. The Research Interns will conduct cutting edge research at the intersection... of computer vision, virtual reality, machine learning and NLP, work on practical real-world applications, and get insight into how an industry R&D center operates, while receiving mentorship and support from experienced researchers, including IEEE Fellow and ACM Distinguished Scientist.

Responsibilities:

Perform research in general AI-related projects on machine learning, pattern recognition, computer vision, and natural language processing to situation perception and decision-making.

The interns will be in charge of developing novel deep learning, computer vision and NLP algorithms and models including but not limited to the following areas:

1. Deep learning for processing and analyzing images, videos and multimodal data, Image segmentation and object detection, unsupervised representation learning for videos/images and NLP;

2. Generative model (GAN, Diffusion model, VAE), deep image/video/text content generation and editing, neural rendering;

3. LLM model (for example, GPT, LLaMA, BERT, BLOOM, T5, or their variants, etc.), Transformer networks;

4. Multi-modal, CLIP, BLIP, GLIDE, etc;

5. Deep network compression and pruning for end devices;

6. Novel view synthesis and free-viewpoint videos;

7. Neural architecture search (NAS);

8. Security and privacy protection for AI models.

9. 3D modeling, reconstruction, and rendering, structure from motion, multi-view geometry, photometric stereo, texture binding and mapping, 3D/4D data compression, 4D motion temporal consistency, and Virtual Reality;

10. 3D scene reconstruction and localization (e.g., visual odometry, SLAM, structure from motion), multi-sensor calibration;

11. 3D face/pose/body reconstruction/synthesis, human body/face parsing, hand gesture reconstruction, gaze detection, and lip movement synthesis for virtual avatars;

Requirements

Qualifications:

1. Master or higher degree in EE, CS, ME and related areas;

2. Skillful in C/C++, pythons and other languages;

3. Hands-on experiences in developing novel deep learning, computer vision and NLP algorithms and models;

Preferred Qualifications:

1. Hands-on experiences in using pytorch and/or tensorflow to develop algorithms and models independently;

2. Have publications in top-tier conferences and journals in the related areas;

Benefits

OPPO is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements.

The US base salary range for this full-time position is $30-$60/hour. Our salary ranges are determined by role, level, and location

The Blockchain Analyst will report to the Sr. Manager, Financial Crimes. The Blockchain Analyst assists with various assignments supporting the Compliance Program of the Company.

In this role, you will...
• Conduct complex investigations into cases that are referred as part of the overall escalation process;
• Conduct proactive blockchain-based investigations;
• Produce briefs and reports on a range of issues:
• Synthesize data derived from other sources into long-form analysis;
• Provide training and support to other analysts on the U.S. Financial Crimes Team;
• Maintain proficiency in all aspects of BSA/AML compliance;
• Attend BSA training as assigned by the Compliance Officer.

Requirements
• Advanced proficiency in blockchain-based investigations, with a minimum of 2 years of relevant experience;
• Nuanced understanding of blockchain technology;
• In-depth knowledge of BSA/AML regulations;
• Experience conducting complex investigations that involve multiple sources of data;
• Advanced written and verbal communication skills;
• Good time management skills;
• Ability to work well under pressure and to manage multiple tasks simultaneously.

Preferred Skills & Experience
• Relevant certifications or coursework
• Experience conducting open source research/OSINT
• Familiarity with the modus operandi of threat actors operating in the cryptocurrency space
• Proficiency in a second language

Michigan State University Global IDEAS of International Studies and Programs supports international engagement under the MSU strategic plan, communicates key data to university leadership and the public, and acts as a campus wide analytical resource. Global IDEAS values individual and group differences and encourage applicants who will contribute to a culture of inclusion on campus.

Global IDEAS... manages MSU’s International Data Portal. This portal currently provides visualizations of or MSU’s Externally Funded International Projects, International Student Enrollment, Education Abroad, International Agreements Data and International Research Collaboration. The process used to display this data currently uses a laborious and incomplete method to access and display the data. Recent conversations with the data managers at MSU have shown a path forward that will allow for direct access and visualization of the data. This access will also allow the construction of personalized dashboards in Tableau for data analysis and display. In addition, there are many ways that MSU’s international work can be analyzed and presented to decision-makers for more complete and thorough use of the data. Global IDEAS seeks a Data Scientist to lead this work and deepen and broaden the collaborations with decision-makers and other Data Scientists across MSU to provide timely analysis and insights.

Global IDEAS seeks a Data Scientist who is curious, creative, and can both see the big picture and work with attention to detail. The successful candidate will have strong interpersonal and communication skills to convey findings to a variety of audiences and positively influence university leadership. The Data Scientist will need to articulate complex issues to non-technical audience clearly and effectively. Daily activities may include development of data representations and visualizations, advising on predictive models and creating easy to understand reports and dashboards.

Primary responsibilities include:
• Analysis and decision support for university international initiatives and projects;
• Consult with units or groups working through specialized data needs and analytics, working as a resource from the beginning to end of the project;
• Analyze, interpret, summarize, and present data and findings in a clear, comprehensive, and effective manner to all levels of the university community;
• Liaise with ISP Directors and leadership to determine data and analytic needs and provide solutions and provide targeted training of tools and platforms when necessary;
• Represent ISP on university wide committees;
• Keep apprised of trends and conversations about higher education;
• Conduct internal and external benchmarking analysis;
• Organize and prioritize a variety of projects in a timely manner, manage own work and priorities;
• Builds custom SQL to meet reporting requirements and ISP International Data Portal;
• Performs query tuning and root cause analysis to optimize performance and fix errors in existing database objects, ensure the quality of the ISP International Data Portal; works with ISP leaders to further enhance data access and presentation in International Data Portal;
• Develop SQL to create database tables, views, and stored procedures to support data storage and report development;
• Develop and design reports and dashboards in Tableau; and
• Consult with and support ISP centers and units with strategic international data analyses and, on a priority basis, collaborate with other units on campus on evaluating and acquiring data tools and streamlining data reporting, use research findings to make recommendations to administrators to contribute to decision making for short- and long-term planning.

Equal Employment Opportunity Statement

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, citizenship, age, disability or protected veteran status.

Required Degree

Doctorate -statistics, computational science or related

Minimum Requirements
• Doctorate degree in statistics, computational science, a social science discipline, GIS, data analytics or related field including other degrees with a strong quantitative emphasis;
• Five or more years of experience in statistical consulting, research, data mining, data science, data management and analysis; or an equivalent combination of education and experience;
• Strong track record demonstrating success in collaborative research projects;
• Excellent communication skills including: presenting, editing, and writing as well as accuracy and attention to detail required;
• Three to five years of related experience in data analysis, SQL development, data warehousing and data visualization; and
• Experience writing advanced SQL queries; expertise with Oracle PL/SQL, expertise with Tableau.

Desired Qualifications
• In depth knowledge of University administrative organization, policies, procedures, and practices for institutional research-oriented roles;
• Ability to use data retrieval and manipulation, and expertise in statistical tools such as SAS, SQL, STATA, R, D3, Python, and data visualization tools such as Tableau;
• Proven excellence in program management and project management;
• Experience building and leading teams across a wide variety of domains;
• Prior experience working in a university setting and with higher education related data (student, research, business support systems). An understanding of data warehouse technologies (Oracle preferred); familiarity with data integration processes using enterprise ETL tools (DataStage preferred) and the role of data stewardship;
• Experience creating data flow diagrams and data dictionaries. The ability to model and analyze data in statistical tools (SPSS, R, SAS, Python, or similar) combined with experience integrating large datasets from a variety of sources. Experience with ETL tools (DataStage, Informatica);
• Ability to use data retrieval and manipulation, and expertise in statistical tools such as SAS, SQL, STATA, R, D3, Python, and data visualization tools such as Tableau; and
• Experience in development and design of reports and dashboards in Tableau and ability to work closely with clients to build custom dashboards and provide support for data analysis to support ISP centers and other units in developing and streamlining data reporting; use research findings to make recommendations to administrators to contribute to decision making for short- and long-term planning.

Required Application Materials
• CV,
• cover letter, and
• sample of work

Remote Work Statement

MSU strives to provide a flexible work environment and this position has been designated as remote-friendly. Remote-friendly means some or all of the duties can be performed remotely as mutually agreed upon.

Website

https://globalideas.isp.msu.edu/

Department Statement

Our Mission

Global Innovations in Development, Engagement, and Scholarship (Global IDEAS) catalyzes interdisciplinary thought, research, and action to solve global/grand challenges in an international development context. We facilitate communities of practice; collaborate and engage with external partners and donors; enhance opportunities for faculty and staff to conduct research, education, and engagement; and provide proposal development and project management to support MSU’s international objectives.

Our Vision

MSU faculty and staff:
• are sought after by partners around the world for collaborative endeavors;
• have increased access to funding sources to support their engagement in international development projects;
• develop competitive and high-quality proposals for impactful projects; and
• are recognized as thought leaders in the international development space and help shape dialogue
